1
00:00:43,240 --> 00:00:44,719
That thing has three eyes.

2
00:00:45,079 --> 00:00:45,600
It looks exactly like the person

3
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:47,560
I just saw on the stone carvings.

4
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:49,920
What person?

5
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:51,119
What did you see just now?

6
00:00:51,119 --> 00:00:52,000
Didn't I fall into

7
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,799
that red-backed toad's mud pit earlier?

8
00:00:53,799 --> 00:00:54,799
There were five stone slabs,

9
00:00:54,799 --> 00:00:56,920
clearly arranged according to Feng Shui.

10
00:00:57,280 --> 00:00:59,880
I think the carvings on them have a deeper meaning.

11
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:02,679
What exactly was on those carvings?

12
00:01:02,759 --> 00:01:04,040
On the first slab,

13
00:01:04,079 --> 00:01:05,519
there was a man with three eyes

14
00:01:05,519 --> 00:01:06,879
struggling in the ocean.

15
00:01:07,359 --> 00:01:08,560
On the second slab,

16
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:10,040
the third eye disappeared,

17
00:01:10,159 --> 00:01:12,519
and he was on an ice field

18
00:01:12,519 --> 00:01:13,560
that was being destroyed.

19
00:01:13,799 --> 00:01:15,120
On the third slab,

20
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:17,760
a strange machine sank with the continent.

21
00:01:18,159 --> 00:01:20,159
The fourth one showed a rain of fire.

22
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:22,120
On the fifth one,

23
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:23,280
the sun was infinitely large,

24
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:24,400
and the world was destroyed.

25
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:26,920
Isn't that the story of

26
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:28,400
the Five Suns from the Mayan civilization?

27
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:29,879
Why is the Mayan civilization popping up here?

28
00:01:29,879 --> 00:01:30,840
This is a total mess.

29
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,079
We're in Nanyun!

30
00:01:32,239 --> 00:01:33,359
What about that bug?

31
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:35,439
This is from the first sun era,

32
00:01:35,439 --> 00:01:36,920
the Gendayan civilization.

33
00:01:37,159 --> 00:01:38,519
Men had a third eye,

34
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:40,359
and it ended with the continent sinking.

35
00:01:40,519 --> 00:01:41,959
The third eye also disappeared.

36
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:43,079
Does this mean

37
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:45,280
its weak point is that third eye?

38
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,400
Exactly.

39
00:01:46,599 --> 00:01:48,159
The eye is always more fragile than the skin.

40
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:51,200
Let's try it as a last resort.

41
00:01:51,719 --> 00:01:52,439
Fatty,

42
00:01:52,519 --> 00:01:53,239
draw its fire!

43
00:01:53,319 --> 00:01:54,040
I'll shoot it.

44
00:01:54,079 --> 00:01:54,760
Go!

45
00:01:55,319 --> 00:01:57,239
One, two, three!

46
00:02:00,159 --> 00:02:01,000
You bastard!

47
00:02:01,239 --> 00:02:02,560
Your grandpa is right here!

48
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,280
Commander Chen, shoot!

49
00:02:23,719 --> 00:02:25,000
It's... It's not working!

50
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,120
Hold this.

51
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:38,919
Shutong, hold this end of the rope.

52
00:02:39,759 --> 00:02:40,479
What for?

53
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:41,599
Fatty,

54
00:02:41,599 --> 00:02:42,400
cover me!

55
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:42,879
Wait,

56
00:02:42,879 --> 00:02:43,639
cover me!

57
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:44,759
Be careful!

58
00:02:51,759 --> 00:02:52,240
Bro!

59
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:53,319
Bro!

60
00:02:54,599 --> 00:02:55,599
He ran away?

61
00:02:56,199 --> 00:02:57,000
Impossible.

62
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:58,240
Old Chen isn't that kind of person.

63
00:03:09,479 --> 00:03:10,240
Commander Chen!

64
00:03:16,639 --> 00:03:17,520
What are you doing?

65
00:03:24,919 --> 00:03:25,800
Big toad!

66
00:03:25,919 --> 00:03:26,719
Get back, get back!

67
00:04:23,319 --> 00:04:24,120
Be careful!

68
00:04:51,519 --> 00:04:52,319
Chen Youxi!

69
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:54,879
Are you okay? I'm fine.

70
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:58,040
Old Chen!

71
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:58,800
Hurry, hurry, hurry!

72
00:05:00,439 --> 00:05:01,040
How is it?

73
00:05:01,279 --> 00:05:02,000
I'm fine.

74
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,480
It's really spectacular.

75
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:36,839
Commander Chen, not bad.

76
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:39,319
Lord Fatty officially grants you

77
00:05:39,319 --> 00:05:41,360
the title of Special Combat Hero.

78
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,560
Brave and fearless.

79
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:43,959
Brave my foot!

80
00:05:45,519 --> 00:05:46,839
How many times have I told you?

81
00:05:46,839 --> 00:05:48,560
Don't act on your own without permission.

82
00:05:48,839 --> 00:05:50,600
Do you know how dangerous it was just now?

83
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,759
Didn't you promise me?

84
00:05:51,759 --> 00:05:52,800
You owe me so much debt.

85
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:53,680
If you die,

86
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:54,519
who's going to pay it back?

87
00:05:55,079 --> 00:05:55,800
No, no, no, how did I...

88
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,759
Ad-Ad-Advisor He.

89
00:05:56,759 --> 00:05:57,519
Well,

90
00:05:58,639 --> 00:05:59,319
it's like this.

91
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:03,439
Death is nothing to a hero.

92
00:06:04,319 --> 00:06:07,439
It's for the happiness of all mankind

93
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:09,240
that one must inevitably experience.

94
00:06:10,079 --> 00:06:12,000
His body

95
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:14,279
will forever rest here,

96
00:06:14,319 --> 00:06:16,879
in the colorful clouds where flowers never fade.

97
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,079
This line is no good.

98
00:06:18,079 --> 00:06:18,920
This line is no good.

99
00:06:19,959 --> 00:06:21,759
He is brave and fearless.

100
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:24,399
He strides forward.

101
00:06:27,199 --> 00:06:29,399
I didn't realize you've gotten so glib.

102
00:06:30,199 --> 00:06:30,879
Advisor He,

103
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:32,800
why don't you discover more about me?

104
00:06:33,399 --> 00:06:34,160
No, no, no.

105
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,800
Bro, Sister Shutong,

106
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:36,879
come and take a look.

107
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:46,439
Its tail is connected to the rock.

108
00:06:47,759 --> 00:06:50,199
I think this thousand-legged immortal bug

109
00:06:50,279 --> 00:06:51,920
and the petrified wood we encountered earlier

110
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,920
experienced crustal movement at the same time.

111
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:57,160
Then this thousand-legged immortal bug

112
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:59,879
might have encountered magma and mudslides simultaneously.

113
00:07:00,399 --> 00:07:01,879
Before the magma could melt

114
00:07:01,879 --> 00:07:03,040
its hard body,

115
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:05,160
it was cooled by the subsequent mudslide.

116
00:07:05,319 --> 00:07:06,040
Therefore,

117
00:07:06,639 --> 00:07:09,800
its tail became fused with this cave.

118
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,600
And because of its characteristics,

119
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,279
even if its tail is fused with the mountain,

120
00:07:13,279 --> 00:07:14,480
it can still survive.

121
00:07:14,639 --> 00:07:16,000
That reminds me of something.

122
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,160
The Mountain God Temple.

123
00:07:17,319 --> 00:07:19,399
Remember the little imp next to the Mountain God?

124
00:07:20,319 --> 00:07:22,360
The offering it was holding in its hands,

125
00:07:23,279 --> 00:07:24,439
wasn't it a toad?

126
00:07:25,399 --> 00:07:27,439
Could it be that this thousand-legged immortal bug

127
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,319
is the Mountain God worshipped by the locals?

128
00:07:30,439 --> 00:07:32,519
You know, these locals are pretty funny.

129
00:07:33,079 --> 00:07:34,720
Worshipping a giant bug as a god.

130
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,639
Didn't the Tomb Suppression Record say it?

131
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,959
After the King of Dian obtained the Lingxiao Pearl,

132
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,759
he came into this Gu Valley

133
00:07:40,759 --> 00:07:42,079
and built the Tomb of the King of Dian.

134
00:07:42,079 --> 00:07:44,560
He wanted to live forever and become an immortal.

135
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,759
Why is there an earthquake?

136
00:07:53,879 --> 00:07:54,800
Old Chen, look!

137
00:07:58,639 --> 00:07:59,439
The bug!

138
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,120
Let's go!

139
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,199
Hurry! Go, go, go!

140
00:08:06,279 --> 00:08:06,879
Go!

141
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,759
This time, it's completely dead, right?

142
00:09:24,799 --> 00:09:26,320
It's not dead.

143
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:28,039
This thousand-legged immortal bug...

144
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:30,799
Its nervous system and body are separated.

145
00:09:30,799 --> 00:09:32,320
Even if its body dies,

146
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,679
its nervous system still survives.

147
00:09:34,679 --> 00:09:35,519
Stop talking, stop talking.

148
00:09:35,519 --> 00:09:36,519
I'm begging you.

149
00:09:36,679 --> 00:09:38,240
If you say more, I'm going to throw up.

150
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:43,440
Commander Chen.

151
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,080
What is this?

152
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:48,600
It's a box, right?

153
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,360
A box?

154
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,120
This guy eats a pretty mixed diet.

155
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:57,519
Could this be the legendary box

156
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,039
filled with evil that can

157
00:09:59,679 --> 00:10:00,480
destroy the world?

158
00:10:08,159 --> 00:10:08,919
Legend has it

159
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:09,960
that this box

160
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,720
is filled with all the evil in the world.

161
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:12,639
Once opened,

162
00:10:12,639 --> 00:10:13,960
the world will be destroyed.

163
00:10:14,399 --> 00:10:18,399
So it's also called the source of disaster.

164
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,080
If that's the case,

165
00:10:21,799 --> 00:10:22,919
let's quit while we're ahead.

166
00:10:22,919 --> 00:10:23,799
Quit while we're ahead.

167
00:10:23,799 --> 00:10:24,679
The big bug is dead too.

168
00:10:24,679 --> 00:10:25,600
Let's go, let's go quickly.

169
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,840
Go? Why should we go?

170
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:29,519
We are the glorious archaeological advance team.

171
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:32,159
We are the glorious descendants of Yan and Huang.

172
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:34,159
How can we be scared by a legend?

173
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:36,679
Get it out and open it up.

174
00:10:37,039 --> 00:10:38,519
Commander Chen, let's go.

175
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:57,799
One end is a dragon and the other is a tiger.

176
00:11:58,360 --> 00:12:00,039
Anyway, just insert it here.

177
00:12:02,519 --> 00:12:03,279
Commander Chen,

178
00:12:03,919 --> 00:12:04,879
you've been staring blankly for a while.

179
00:12:05,519 --> 00:12:06,720
What are you thinking about?

180
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,399
I have a question.

181
00:12:09,799 --> 00:12:10,759
What question?

182
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:12,600
He is wondering

183
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:15,360
whether to insert the dragon or tiger head first.

184
00:12:17,159 --> 00:12:18,840
Advisor He really understands me.

185
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,320
Nonsense.

186
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,039
What's your opinion?

187
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:24,519
All right, all right.

188
00:12:24,519 --> 00:12:26,519
This has nothing to do with understanding you.

189
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,600
Just close your eyes,

190
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:29,600
who cares which end, just shove it in.

191
00:12:37,639 --> 00:12:39,080
From the perspective of the ancients,

192
00:12:39,399 --> 00:12:41,120
in their secret feng shui arts,

193
00:12:41,919 --> 00:12:44,399
changing the feng shui layout has another term.

194
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:46,039
It's called the standoff between dragon and tiger.

195
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,480
The standoff between dragon and tiger?

196
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:51,799
The ancients believed that this standoff

197
00:12:51,799 --> 00:12:54,120
represents the regulation of yin and yang.

198
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:56,120
Changing the layout's form and energy

199
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:59,120
relies on the delicate balance of clear and turbid energies.

200
00:12:59,399 --> 00:13:00,159
If

201
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:02,960
the dragon and tiger are reversed,

202
00:13:03,399 --> 00:13:05,559
it's easy to mess up the clear and turbid energies.

203
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:07,519
From the logical thinking of the ancients,

204
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,240
the ancient ruins area behind Ailong Mountain,

205
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:11,799
its feng shui layout is half artificial, half natural.

206
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:13,840
The tomb-guarding record under the banyan tree,

207
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:15,799
the nine-bend winding path facing the mountain shore,

208
00:13:15,879 --> 00:13:17,480
the gourd-shaped entrance outside the mountain god temple,

209
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:19,279
and the five-five plum blossom array in the mud pit.

210
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:21,600
These treasure caves were all modified.

211
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:24,399
As the saying goes, going against heaven's will.

212
00:13:24,919 --> 00:13:27,360
This is an act that violates the laws of nature.

213
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:31,879
What happens if it gets messed up?

214
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:35,600
At best, it will show an ominous form.

215
00:13:36,279 --> 00:13:37,519
At worst?

216
00:13:37,559 --> 00:13:39,919
It will lead to wind, ants, and water,

217
00:13:40,240 --> 00:13:41,799
the three hazards invading the cave.

218
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:42,840
The harm is endless.

219
00:13:43,039 --> 00:13:45,000
But if the order is wrong,

220
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:46,759
what will happen to this box?

221
00:13:48,919 --> 00:13:50,159
Everyone will be gone.

222
00:13:50,159 --> 00:13:50,840
Come on.

223
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:52,000
Dragon head or tiger head,

224
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:54,000
each carries a fifty percent risk.

225
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:55,960
Even if this box has traps,

226
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:57,679
it's nothing more than poison gas or hidden arrows.

227
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,399
If we take protective measures,

228
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:00,519
there shouldn't be any problem.

229
00:14:00,879 --> 00:14:02,559
According to the principles of Qingwu,

230
00:14:02,639 --> 00:14:04,679
we might as well take the clear yang energy first,

231
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:06,600
which is safer,

232
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:08,240
the dragon head.

233
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:41,440
Okay.

234
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:42,279
Open one

235
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:43,840
to prove that it's right.

236
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:45,000
Hurry up and unscrew it.
